'''Devante McKain''' (born 26 June 1994) is an English [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for [[Bedford Town F.C.|Bedford Town]] as a [[Defender (association football)|defender]].

==Club career==
McKain began his youth career at [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]] before eventually moving on to [[Maidenhead United F.C.|Maidenhead United]]. In November 2012, McKain signed for [[Gillingham F.C.|Gillingham]] for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kentnews.co.uk/mobile/sport/gillingham_sign_devante_mckain_from_maidenhead_1_1684676|title=Kent News|accessdate=23 June 2014|publisher=Kent News|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20140623144616/http://www.kentnews.co.uk/mobile/sport/gillingham_sign_devante_mckain_from_maidenhead_1_1684676|archivedate=23 June 2014|df=dmy-all}}</ref> At the time, then [[Gillingham F.C.|Gillingham]] boss [[Martin Allen]] said "Devante was recommended to me by Maidenhead United manager Johnson Hippolyte, the same man that recommended DJ Campbell to me."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kentnews.co.uk/mobile/sport/gillingham_sign_devante_mckain_from_maidenhead_1_1684676|title=Kent News|accessdate=23 June 2014|publisher=Kent News|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20140623144616/http://www.kentnews.co.uk/mobile/sport/gillingham_sign_devante_mckain_from_maidenhead_1_1684676|archivedate=23 June 2014|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Allen also said of McKain "He is big. He is strong. He is quick. He heads it. He needs to improve technically but he has got priceless attributes for a young centre-back."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kentnews.co.uk/mobile/sport/gillingham_sign_devante_mckain_from_maidenhead_1_1684676|title=Kent News|accessdate=23 June 2014|publisher=Kent News|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20140623144616/http://www.kentnews.co.uk/mobile/sport/gillingham_sign_devante_mckain_from_maidenhead_1_1684676|archivedate=23 June 2014|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Also at the time, [[Maidenhead United F.C.|Maidenhead United]] manager [[Johnson Hippolyte]] said of McKain, "from day one we were all adamant he would play professional football. It was a no brainer, that's how much ability he has."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thenonleaguefootballpaper.com/latest-news/conference-south-step-three/1950/devante-mckain-steps-up-to-join-gillingham/|title=thenonleaguefootballpaper|accessdate=23 June 2014|publisher=thenonleaguefootballpaper}}</ref>

McKain made his [[Football League One]] debut for [[Gillingham F.C.|Gillingham]] on 27 April 2013 at [[Burton Albion F.C.|Burton Albion]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.soccerbase.com/players/player.sd?player_id=63202/|title=Soccerbase|accessdate=24 July 2014|publisher=Soccerbase}}</ref> On 7 September 2013, he made his second [[Gillingham F.C.|Gillingham]] appearance against [[Crawley Town F.C.|Crawley Town]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.soccerbase.com/players/player.sd?player_id=63202/|title=Soccerbase|accessdate=24 July 2014|publisher=Soccerbase}}</ref>

In October 2013, [[Martin Allen]] said, "Devante was close to playing in our team a couple of weeks ago. He has been fantastic in training."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kentonline.co.uk/kent/sport/allen-u-turn-on-hess-7293/|title=Kent News|accessdate=23 June 2014|publisher=Kent News}}</ref>

In May 2014, McKain signed a new one-year deal to stay at [[Gillingham F.C.|Gillingham]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www1.skysports.com/football/news/11737/9304269/gills-trio-win-pro-deals|title=skysports|accessdate=23 June 2014|publisher=skysports}}</ref>

In March 2015, Devante was released by Gillingham along with several others <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/32139017|title=bbc sport|accessdate=31 March 2015|publisher=bbc sport}}</ref>

